], [32, 2], [33, 0], [33, 2], [33, 4], [33, 6], [33, 8], [33, 10], [33, 12], [33, 14], [33, 16], [33, 18], [33, 20], [33, 22], [33, 24], [33, 26], [33, 28], [33, 30], [33, 32], [33, 34], [34, 0], [34, 2], [34, 4], [34, 6], [34, 8], [34, 10], [34, 12], [34, 14], [34, 16], [34, 18], [35, 0], [35, 2], [36, 0], [36, 2], [37, 0], [37, 2], [38, 0], [38, 2], [39, 0], [39, 2], [39, 4], [39, 6], [39, 8], [40, 0], [40, 2], [40, 4], [40, 6], [40, 8], [41, 0], [41, 2], [41, 4], [41, 6], [41, 8], [41, 10], [41, 12], [42, 0]]}, "lines": {"text": ["National Grid Community Relations Team", "JBP", "Freephone: 0800 073 1047", "Third Floor, 34 Smith Square", "nationalgridteam@jbp.co.uk", "Westminster, London, SW1P 3HL", "www.nationalgrid.com", "Councillor Robert Ward", "Selsdon and Addington Village ward, Croydon Council", "robert.ward@croydon.gov.uk", "20 July 2021", "Dear Councillor Ward", "Beddington to Rowdown cable replacement \u2013 project update", "I thought it\u2019d be useful to send you an update about the replacement of the underground electricity cable", "We need to carry out our essential work to ensure we keep between Beddington and Rowdown substations.", "the transmission network in first-class working order and help meet future electricity demands. Our work", "represents a substantial investment in the region\u2019s power network.\u202f", "We\u2019re now in the latter stages of the project. However, due to delays because of the Covid-19 pandemic and", "the knock-on effect to the supply chain, we expect our work will continue until Spring 2022.", "The replacement is complete, and we\u2019ll now concentrate on testing the new cable. We\u2019ll take away the old", "cable, equipment, and materials from our working areas later this year and carry out some reinstatement", "work, including resurfacing and fence repairs. We\u2019ll then remove our site office cabins from Rowdown", "substation and stone chippings from a temporary haul road off Mickleham Way which leads to the substation.", "This will bring most of our work to an end with only minor electrical works continuing within the substations", "until Spring 2022. None of our work will affect local electricity supplies.", "We\u2019ll keep our site neighbours informed as our work progresses on-site. I hope you find this this summary", "helpful. You can find more details about the project on our webpage", "https://www.nationalgrid.com/uk/electricity-transmission/infrastructure-projects/beddington-rowdown", "One final thing to mention is our Voices for A Green Future schools\u2019 competition, which gives the next", "generation a voice on the journey to a clean energy future. We\u2019ve written to schools to encourage them to", "enter. The winners will have their speeches premiered at the UN Climate Change Conference later this year,", "of which we\u2019re the principal partner. If you\u2019d like to send it on to any local contacts here\u2019s the link for more", "information https://www.nationalgrid.com/cop26/voices-for-a-green-future/resources.", "If you have any queries about this scheme, please contact our Community Relations team on 0800 073 1047", "or email nationalgridteam@jbp.co.uk. They\u2019re available daily from 7am to 7pm.", "Yours sincerely", "Lara Chilcott", "Project Manager", "National Grid", "National Grid Electricity Transmission plc", "1-3 Strand, London WC2N 5EH", "Registered in England and Wales, No 2366977", "1"], "bbox": [[0.073814, 0.041934, 0.24822400000000006, 0.009546], [0.073814, 0.055046, 0.024738999999999997, 0.009546], [0.359798, 0.06716, 0.16239999999999993, 0.009546], [0.073814, 0.068158, 0.172686, 0.009546], [0.359798, 0.077991, 0.16688700000000006, 0.009546], [0.073814, 0.081269, 0.20112199999999997, 0.009546], [0.359798, 0.088965, 0.13165299999999996, 0.009546], [0.074016, 0.158748, 0.174478, 0.011825], [0.074016, 0.17243, 0.40344500000000005, 0.011825], [0.074016, 0.185969, 0.215894, 0.011825], [0.738554, 0.199651, 0.095217, 0.011825], [0.074016, 